&lt;li&gt;Own marketing and sales reporting for leadership and our commercial team. Draw on data from Salesforce, Webflow, Google Ads, Google Analytics, and other sources.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as subject matter expert for all online marketing data sources. Be the backstop for accuracy and guarantee the validity of reports and metrics presented to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze cost-per-click, cost-per-lead, and click-through-rates and advise on how to optimize marketing performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally to identify and deliver the best paid media opportunities to drive business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree, preferably in Marketing, Business, Economics, or Data Science&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience creating, delivering, and interpreting commercial reports drawing from Salesforce, Google AdWords, Google Analytics, Webflow, and other digital marketing data sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a demonstrated track record identifying and resolving inconsistencies in commercial data to drive B2B growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A perfectionist approach and ownership mentality toward analysis and reporting metrics. You take the ramifications of data-guided decision-making seriously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience presenting reports to leadership in a team setting from a marketing, finance, or consulting perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

